Test Case ID	Test Case Title	Module	Priority	Preconditions	Step #	Test Step (Action)	Expected Result
E2E-01	Battery Failure Lifecycle (WXP-only, Pro/Elite)	Alert Generation & Lifecycle	Critical	Test device enrolled in a Pro/Elite tenant (not Premium-covered). Battery Failure alert rule is enabled with default config. Notification channel (In-product) enabled for IT Admin role.	1	Inject telemetry simulating a battery failure condition for the test device.	Telemetry is accepted by the system without error.
					2	Allow the detection algorithm to evaluate the condition (standard evaluation cycle).	Algorithm correctly identifies the battery failure condition.
					3	Navigate to Active Alerts > PCs.	A new alert titled 'Battery failure detected on device {serial_no}' appears, Severity = Critical, Source = WXP.'
					4	Open the alert details page.	Details show: Severity=Critical, Device serial number (linked), Created timestamp, Updated timestamp, Status=Open, Last signed-in user, OS, Alert ID, Problem code=938, Warranty status, Failure code/details.
					5	Click the device serial number link.	User is navigated to the PC details screen for the correct device.
					6	Verify notification was sent to the IT Admin via the In-product channel.	IT Admin received exactly one in-product notification referencing this alert.
					7	Clear the battery failure condition (resolve via test telemetry).	Telemetry update is accepted.
					8	Allow the daily auto-resolution job to run.	Alert status changes from Open to Resolved.
					9	Wait 24 hours after the alert entered Resolved status (or use test time-acceleration hook).	Alert is automatically removed from the Active Alerts list.
